{{Japanese clans |Name = Tsuge no Kuni no Miyatsuko |Crest image = |Crest Name = |Origin Surname = Tsuge Clan |Ancestor = Unknown |Base Territory = {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|Yamato Province|12=draft|12=draft}}{{ill|Yamabe District|ja|山辺郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, Tsuge |Notable Figures = See [[#Figures|Figures]] |Branches = }} '''Tsuge no Kuni no Miyatsuko''' (つげのくにのみやつこ・つげこくぞう) governed the [[#Territory|Tsuge Province]] (northeastern {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|Yamato Province|12=draft|12=draft}}).
* {{ill|Tsuge no Ōyamanushi|ja|闘鶏大山主|1=Tsuge no Ōyamanushi|12=draft|12=draft}} was a notable figure and is worshipped as an ice god
__TOC__ {{clear}}
== Overview == === Name === The name appears as '''Tsuge no Kuni no Miyatsuko''' in the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|12=draft|12=draft}}, as well as '''Tsuge no Kuni no Miyatsuko''' and '''Tsuge Kuni no Miyatsuko'''.
=== Ancestors === Unknown.
=== Clan === The clan is the '''{{ill|Tsuge Clan|ja|闘鳥氏|12=draft|12=draft}}''' (Tsuge-shi) with the {{ill|Kabane|ja|委姻|12=draft|12=draft}} "{{ill|Kimi (kabane)|ja|君|12=draft|12=draft}}." During the reign of {{ill|Emperor Ingyō|ja|允恭天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}, the clan was demoted to the kabane "{{ill|Inagi|ja|稲穂|12=draft|12=draft}}" due to disrespect shown to {{ill|Oshisaka no Ōnakatsuhime|ja|忍坂大中姫|12=draft|12=draft}}. A related branch held the kabane "{{ill|Atoneri|ja|直|12=draft|12=draft}}."
== Base Territory == The clan was based in {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|Yamato Province|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Yamabe District|ja|山辺郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, in the area of modern-day {{ill|Tsuge Village|ja|都祁村|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Clan Deities == The clan deity may have been '''{{ill|Tsuge Suibun Shrine|ja|都祁水分神社|12=draft|12=draft}}'''. The shrine’s deities are identified as {{ill|Hayakitsuhiko and Hayakitsuhime|ja|速秋津男命|Hayakitsuhiko and Hayakitsuhime=Hayakitsuhiko and Hayakitsuhime|lt=Hayaakitsuhiko-no-Mikoto|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Ōkuni-no-Mitama|ja|大国寡魂命|12=draft|12=draft}}, or {{ill|Mikumari|ja|天之水分神|lt=Ame no Mikumari|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Mikumari|ja|国之水分神|lt=Kuni no Mikumari|12=draft|12=draft}}.
=== Burial Site === * '''{{ill|Sanryōbo Kofun Cluster|ja|三陵墓古坛群|12=draft|12=draft}}''' *: Located in {{ill|Tsuge Minaminosho|ja|都祁南の莊町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県|12=draft|12=draft}}, this Kofun cluster is believed to be associated with the clan.
== Figures == * '''{{ill|Ōyamanu Kimi|ja|大山主君|12=draft|12=draft}}''' *: A governor during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Nintoku|ja|仲徹天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}, credited as the first to present ice from the {{ill|Himuro|ja|氷室|12=draft|12=draft}} (icehouse) to the imperial court, establishing the tradition of managing the icehouses. * '''{{ill|Tsunoko Kimi|ja|角古君|12=draft|12=draft}} (Tsuge no Kuni no Miyatsuko)''' *: A governor during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Ingyō|ja|允恭天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}, demoted to the kabane "Inagi" due to disrespect. His original name is unknown.
== Descendants == * '''{{ill|Tsuge no Mita|ja|闘鳥御田|12=draft|12=draft}}''' *: Also known as {{ill|Inabe no Mita|ja|伊名部御田|12=draft|12=draft}}, he was a master craftsman during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Yūryaku|ja|雄略天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}. His skill in high-altitude construction made him appear to "fly like a bird."
* '''{{ill|Kita Clan|ja|北氏|12=draft|12=draft}}''' *: A powerful family in {{ill|Yamabe District|ja|山辺郡|12=draft|12=draft}} associated with the {{ill|Tsuge Suibun Shrine|ja|都祁水分神社|12=draft|12=draft}} as its priestly line. They later adopted the surname "Fujiwara." == See Also == * {{ill|List of Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|国造の一覧|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Himuro Shrine|ja|氷室神社|12=draft|12=draft}}
== References == * {{Cite book|title=國史大辞典|publisher={{ill|Yoshikawa Kōbunkan|ja|吉川学文館|12=draft|12=draft}}}} * {{Cite book|author=Tarō Sakamoto, Kunio Hirano|title=Japanese Ancient Clan Name Dictionary|publisher={{ill|Yoshikawa Kōbunkan|ja|吉川学文館|12=draft|12=draft}}}} * {{Cite book|title=Japanese History Dictionary|publisher={{ill|Yamakawa Shuppansha|ja|山川出版社|12=draft|12=draft}}}} * {{Cite book|title=Shintō Encyclopedia|publisher={{ill|Rinsen Shoten|ja|臨川書店|12=draft|12=draft}}}}
